latestPosts.caption:
Got NANOBLADED by @browsbysuman ⬇️ Read Below
As a model, outside of work, I don’t like to wear make up - but due to a bad waxing job in 2010 I have gaps in my brows and everyday I don’t leave the house without penciling in my brows… right now, they are intense, but in 10 days my brows will be fully healed and looking natural AF and for the next 6 months (to one year) I’m so f’ing happy I won’t have to put any make up on my face outside of work!! Thank you @browsbysuman for doing such an exceptional job and making this happen ❤️

HUGE January Dump ❤️ What a F*ing Year So Far…
This month so far was full of tears of joy and tears of sadness, having lost my grandmother at the start of the month, I thought maybe I was doomed, but thankfully the universe is so kind to me and gifted me so many beautiful experiences… I got to travel to Bikaner, Delhi, Jaipur, Sri Lanka and Ahmedabad for work, I got to walk for SABYASACHI, Shoot for Manish Malhotra, Do a W Campaign, Shoot 2 Jewellery Campaigns + Shoot for some Amazing Indian and Pakistani clients. I’ve gotten to spend time with so many beautiful humans, I’ve met so many new beautiful people, I’ve attend some epic events and gifted so many memorable moments full of love, kindness, gratitude and joy! I’ve learnt so many things about myself already this year which I hope will shape me into a better human being and I can’t wait to see what else is in store in the next chapter of my life story… stay tuned for February 🥹

latestPosts.caption:
Who wants to take me shopping? lol 😝 read below 🔽

Did you know, I am a minimalist and have never owned any branded clothes, bags or accessories in my life? As a model it’s expected of me, but I’m so basic when it comes to my wardrobe and I’ve never found any of these big branded clothing so interesting that I’m to spend my hard earned money on it. As a model you mostly hussle and most of the time I never get paid on time so I always have to save money just incase, even being a so called supermodel in India, I don’t make the kind of money supermodels do in America. It has however been a dream of mine to walk the runway for these brands in a fashion show at NYFW or in Paris & Italy but I’ve not been lucky enough to get agencies in these countries because I’m too big (even though I’m a small size)… but as a 34 year old model, I’m not sure I’ll get to chance now. It’s been a dream not because I’ve loved the clothes so much, but because I’ve been fed the idea that if I shoot for these brands I’ve ’made it’ as a model. Today, because of the overwhelming number of models coming into the industry and there being no regulations in the industry, models are prepared to work for lower rates or free, so day by day, the rates of modelling jobs are going down and even models now who walk for these shows or shoot for these brands are getting less money every year! I’m kinda worried for the industry but I thank the universe that I have regular and exceptional work coming in from the brands I work for because of India & I really love my life here… being a minimalist and not throwing away my money on fancy expensive clothing, I save my money and spend it where it really counts, having experiences that shape my mind, body and soul; like travelling, adventurous activities, hobbies and investing it to set up a secure future for myself… 

.

.

.
